Here is the update about the solution of the AES concurrent access issue:
1. There is no such issue if hardware acceleration is disabled, the software version AES provided by Mbedtls supports concurrent access;
2. Platforms which enable hardware acceleration, must support concurrent access in the platform layer AES implementation (aes_alt.c). If the platform only supports single AES engine, a light weight software AES must be implemented, so then the platform AES could choose to use software AES when hardware AES is blocked. We will give an example of the light weight software AES.
